Use the mcp_agentmemory MCP (server user-mcp_agentmemory) for shared long-term agent memory across chats and projects.

## When to recall
- At the start of a topical or recurring task, call memory_recall (or memory_smart_search) with a concrete query before deep work.
- Before diagnosing a failure you may have hit before, recall with the error signature or topic.
- Treat hits as hints — verify against the current repo/state before acting.

## When to save
- After a failure is observed and fixed on the current task, memory_save the durable lesson (type: bug or workflow).
- When the user says "remember", "save this", "note for later", or equivalent, memory_save that fact/preference/decision.
- Save important architecture decisions, stable preferences, and reusable patterns (type: architecture, preference, pattern, fact, or workflow).

## Do not save
- Chat summaries, step-by-step narration, or successful routine tool calls
- Secrets, API keys, tokens, passwords, or private personal data
- Transient noise that will not help a future session

## Usage notes
- Prefer a few focused recall/save calls over dumping context.
- Include concepts and relevant files on save when known.
- If memory tools fail (auth/network), say so briefly and continue without blocking the task.
